text.tspan: Children per woman that survived childhood vs those that died in childhood,
The total height of the red and green areas shows the average number of children born per woman up to the present. The area
in red shows the average number of children an average woman gave birth to, who died within the first five years of life.
Source: OWID calculations based on Gapminder data
